article.headline: Stetson 75, Gardner Webb 66
article.story: DELAND, Fla. (AP) -- Gabe McMillen scored a career-high 19 points and handed out seven assists to lead Stetson to a 77-65 victory over Gardner-Webb on Saturday. McMillen didn't miss a shot all night, making two 3-pointers, six other field goals and his only free throw. E.J. Gordon, playing his final home game, led all scorers with 21 points to help the Hatters (13-17, 11-9) win their eighth straight game. It marks Stetson's longest win streak since the 1982-83 team won its first eight games. The Bulldogs are 17-11 overall and 13-7 in conference play. Stetson led by just one point after Gardner-Webb's Tim Jennings made a 3-pointer to make it a 52-51 game with 9:43 to play. But the Hatters scored the next 14 points with McMillen having a hand in most of them. McMillen made a three-point play, a 3-pointer and had two assists in the 14-0 run that covered 2:16 and left Stetson with a 66-51 lead. Anthony Register finished with 17 points for Stetson. Jennings led Gardner-Webb with 18 points, while Simon Conn had 15 points.
